Ensure your local MongoDB instance is running, as the `.env` file will default to `mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/node-boilerplate`.

---
MONGODB_URL=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/node-express-boilerplate

### Step 2: Implement the Health Check Feature (Day 2)
This feature will monitor the exact state of the MongoDB connection and report it back to the client.

1. Create a new file at `src/controllers/health.controller.js`.
2. Add the following connection logic:
   ```javascript
   const mongoose = require('mongoose');

   const checkHealth = async (req, res) => {
     const dbStatus = mongoose.connection.readyState;
     
     const statusMap = {
       0: 'Disconnected',
       1: 'Connected',
       2: 'Connecting',
       3: 'Disconnecting'
     };

     const healthCheck = {
       uptime: process.uptime(),
       message: 'OK',
       timestamp: Date.now(),
       services: {
         database: statusMap[dbStatus] || 'Unknown'
       }
     };

     if (dbStatus === 1) {
       res.status(200).send(healthCheck);
     } else {
       healthCheck.message = 'Degraded';
       res.status(503).send(healthCheck);
     }
   };

   module.exports = {
     checkHealth,
   };